gy of language, colonial discourse analysis).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGlobalization. 0aLanguage and sex. 0aMultilingualism. 4aDiskursanalyse. 4aGender. 4aGlobalisierung. 4aSprachsoziologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aSociolinguistics.  adiscourse analysis.  agender.  aglobalization.1 aBesnier, Niko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBucholtz, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaudio, Rudolf P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeller, Monica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInoue, Miyako, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcElhinny, Bonnie S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcElhinny, Bonnie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiskimmin, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNguyen, Binh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhilips, Susan U., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPujolar, Joan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeidman, Amanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYang, Jie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZhang, Qing, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Social Sciences 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023853208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Social Sciences 2000 - 2014z978311063